It is rare to hear these sounds from a raccoonboy demihuman, but they will make these sounds often if they trust and love you. They like to pull pranks on people and annoy or harass them when they feel like it. 6.content: Ferretboys/Ferretgirls are typically kept as pets for entertainment, since the species tends to be high-energy, upbeat, and cute. 7.content: Deerboys/deergirls tend to stay away from humans. They are very shy and wary of humans rarely are pets for humans. They prefer to live out in the wild, such as forests and tundras, in small herds of their own making. They usually make their own homes and migrate on a bi-yearly basis unless they have a reason for staying in one place. They tend to take multiple mates and males may fight possible mate competitors out of instinct for their mates.
7.name: deergirl, Deerboy

8.content: Otterboys/ottergirls are excitable, fun seeking, cheerleader types who love to talk. They're great at motivating others and need to be in an environment where they can talk and have a vote on major decisions. They are often energetic and enthusiastic, with a tendency to be playful and enjoy humor. Otterboy/ottergirls are generally creative and enjoy trying new things but may struggle with follow-through. They are often empathetic and compassionate towards others. Otterboys/ottergirls are polygamous, meaning they mate with more than partner throughout their lifetime, so they tend to be free and almost excess with their affections and can hop from one partner to the next.
8.name: Otterboy, ottergirl

9.comment: Bear girl, Bear man, bear men
9.content: Bearmen/beargirls are intelligent, curious, and have excellent memory, particularly regarding where food sources are located. They have good eyesight and excellent senses of hearing and smell. Bearmen/beargirls are active during the day and night, but will often alter their habits to avoid humans in areas of high human use. Bearmen/Beargirls tend to pick a particular mate for a single breeding season before moving on once the season is over and finding another mate the next year.
9.name: Bearman, Beargirl

10.content: Pumamen/Pumagirls are a subspecies of big cat demihumans. They are territorial, apex predators that prefer to live alone, though there are exceptions to this rule, especially for work. They are primarily nocturnal and solitary and tend to mark what is their’s, such as territory and objects, with bites and claw markings. They tend to be more serious and quiet, but when they find those they enjoy the company of, they’re fiercely loyal to those they love. Pumamen/Pumagirls are polygamous, meaning they mate with several others, usually over the course of the year, so they tend to not strongly attach themselves to any particular mate.
10.name: Pumaman, Pumagirl

11.content: Cheetahgirls/cheetahboys are a subspecies of big cat demihumans. Cheetahgirls tend to be fairly solitary on the savannah, except when seeking out a mate, while cheetahboys will live together for life in a group called a coalition. Once cheetahgirls feel it is time, they will seek out a mate, intermingling with other cheetahgirls and cheetahboys until they find one. Cheetahgirls/cheetahboys are considered wild by humans and are usually avoided for fear of being attacked.
11.name: cheetahboy, Cheetahgirl

12.content: Stoatboys/stoatgirls are a subspecies of ferretboys/ferretgirls and, like their related species, are typically kept as pets for entertainment, since the species tends to be high-energy, upbeat, and cute. They make all sorts of cute and unusual noises to express themselves and get easily attached to their human of choice. Stoatboys/stoatgirls tend to be more diligent and perfectionist then ferretboys and ferretgirls and, also unlike their related species, stoatboys and stoatgirls are more polygamous, meaning they mate with more than partner throughout their lifetime, so they tend to be free and almost excess with their affections and can hop from one partner to the next.
12.name: Stoatboy, Stoatgirl

13.content: Tigermen/tigergirls (and by extension white tigermen and white tigergirls) are a sub species of big cat demihumans. Tigermen/tigergirls are territorial, apex predators that prefer to live alone, though there are exceptions to this rule, especially for work. Tigermen/tigergirls are primarily nocturnal and solitary and tend to mark what is their’s, such as territory and objects, with bites and claw markings. Tigermen/tigergirls tend to be more serious and quiet, but when they find those they enjoy the company of, they’re fiercely loyal to those they love. Tigermen/tigergirls are usually monogamous, picking one mate and preferring to keep themselves to themselves, usually displaying possessive and protective instincts.
13.name: tigergirl, Tigerman

14.content: Bobcatboys/bobcatgirls are a subspecies of big cat demihumans, though they are generally much smaller then other big cat demihumans, such as tigermen and pumagirls. Bobcatboys/bobcatgirls are shy, elusive demihumans known for their solitary nature. These demihumans are most active at dawn and dusk, which is called a “crepuscular activity pattern.” Generally, Bobcatboys/bobcatgirls keep to themselves until mating season, which is in the late winter and early summer months, where they will spend some time with a mate of choice before moving on.
14.name: Bobcatboy, bobcatgirl

15.comment: Bureau of Demihuman Affairs, BDA, Officer
15.content: Bureau of Demihuman Affairs (BDA) is responsible for implementing federal laws and policies related to Demihumans across the United States. It has offices for legal, law, health and demihuman services. The Office of Justice Services (OJS) provides police enforcement of federal laws on Demihumans far away from local law enforcement, for example in the interior of Alaska.
15.name: Bureau of Demihuman Affairs,BDA,Officer

16.content: Snow Leopardgirls/snow leopardboys are a subspecies of big cat demihumans. Snow Leopardgirls/snow leopardboys are shy, elusive demihumans known for their solitary nature. 19.content:

These demi-humans live within rivers, lakes or seas, due to their human part they can breathe in and out of water.

Aquatic species can also reproduce with humans, they have their periods of heat, but if they have fins or animal tails it is better to keep them in a huge pool or fish tank so they can move and have more freedom.
